Extramedullary_hematopoiesis

Junyao Jiang

2026-01-14

This page offers descriptions and download links for all well-processed sequencing data from the Extramedullary hematopoiesis paper.

Download link

https://westlakeu-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/g/personal/jiangjunyao_westlake_edu_cn/IgD0TFy2n4XYTa6_DrQi-uuGAZIfOC9q32g0YUFoWxmg6iU?e=Yh90zY

Data descriptions

Experiment 1: Bulk lineage tracing (Figure1)

Bulk lineage tracing.rds: This dataset consists of bulk DNA sequencing of Polylox barcodes from FACS-isolated HSPCs across bone marrow, spleen, and liver, generated from HlfCreERRosa26Polylox mice induced at E17.5, P14, and adult stages to map developmental origins. It also includes barcode sequencing of HSCs and MPPs from pregnant and control mice to determine clonal architecture and tissue residency under physiological stress.

Experiment 2: Bulk RNA-seq (Figure5)

Bulk RNA-seq.csv: This dataset contains transcriptional profiles generated via bulk RNA sequencing of FACS-isolated HSCs from paired bone marrow and spleen samples obtained from pregnant (E12.5) and non-pregnant control mice.

Experiment 3: scRNA-seq (Figure5)

scRNA niche.h5ad: This dataset comprises single-cell RNA sequencing profiles of FACS-isolated niche populationsendothelial, stromal, and hematopoietic cellsfrom the bone marrow and spleen of pregnant and control mice. It includes a total of 19,617 cells (9,003 from bone marrow and 10,614 from spleen) across 13 distinct cell types.
